Global Microwave Kinetic Inductance Detectors (MKIDs) Market Insights
Microwave Kinetic Inductance Detectors (MKIDs) Market size was valued at USD 0.25 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.75 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 15.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Microwave Kinetic Inductance Detectors (MKIDs) Market Overview
The global Microwave Kinetic Inductance Detectors (MKIDs) market is projected to reach USD 130.5 million by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 17.5% from 2023. MKIDs are key components used in next-generation sensors for astronomy, quantum computing, and particle physics, offering advantages in energy sensitivity, multiplexing capabilities, and fast detection times. The market's growth is primarily driven by the increasing demand for advanced sensors in space research and scientific instrumentation. Furthermore, the technological advancements in detector materials and integration methods contribute to this market's expansion.

